#: ../../source/blog/2019/isolated-clusters/index.rst:134
msgid "Features of multi-mesh deployments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/blog/2019/isolated-clusters/index.rst:136
msgid ""
"**non-uniform naming**. The ``withdraw`` service in the ``accounts`` "
"namespace in one mesh might have different functionality and API than the"
" ``withdraw`` services in the ``accounts`` namespace in other meshes. "
"Such situation could happen in an organization where there is no uniform "
"policy on naming of namespaces and services, or when the meshes belong to"
" different organizations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/blog/2019/isolated-clusters/index.rst:142
msgid ""
"**expose-nothing by default**. None of the services in a mesh are exposed"
" by default, the mesh owners must explicitly specify which services are "
"exposed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/blog/2019/isolated-clusters/index.rst:145
msgid ""
"**boundary protection**. The access control of the traffic must be "
"enforced at the ingress gateway, which stops forbidden traffic from "
"entering the mesh. This requirement implements `Defense-in-depth "
"principle <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Defense_in_depth_(computing)>`_ "
"and is part of some compliance standards, such as the `Payment Card "
"Industry (PCI) Data Security Standard "
"<https://www.pcisecuritystandards.org/pci_security/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/blog/2019/isolated-clusters/index.rst:152
msgid ""
"**common trust may not exist**. The Istio sidecars in one mesh may not "
"trust the Citadel certificates in other meshes, due to some security "
"requirement or due to the fact that the mesh owners did not initially "
"plan to federate the meshes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/blog/2019/isolated-clusters/index.rst:157
msgid ""
"While **expose-nothing by default** and **boundary protection** are "
"required to facilitate compliance and improve security, **non-uniform "
"naming** and **common trust may not exist** are required when connecting "
"meshes of different organizations, or of an organization that cannot "
"enforce uniform naming or cannot or may not establish common trust "
"between the meshes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/blog/2019/isolated-clusters/index.rst:164
msgid ""
"An optional feature that you may want to use is **service location "
"transparency**: consuming services send requests to the exposed services "
"in remote meshes using local service names. The consuming services are "
"oblivious to the fact that some of the destinations are in remote meshes "
"and some are local services. The access is uniform, using the local "
"service names, for example, in Kubernetes, "
"``reviews.default.svc.cluster.local``. **Service location transparency** "
"is useful in the cases when you want to be able to change the location of"
" the consumed services, for example when some service is migrated from "
"private cloud to public cloud, without changing the code of your "
"applications."
msgstr ""

